Sailor friend was telling me how on isolated ships, as in the Arctic ocean, the second mate was supposed to do surgeries during an emergency, using satellite internet to have a Skype call with a medic from the land.

Imagine the ship shaking in a storm, heavy waves crashing, you are holding a scalpel over an Appendicitis patient, a laptop with a 240p webcam is connecting you to an Indian doctor guiding you, signal is on and off, lagging, the room itself is moving. The brutality of sea life!
God bless! Theodore is what I want to name my son one day, it is a great name. Will pray for you and rest of the fam.
